<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,858,1602]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Male 
<quantity box="[216,351,858,883]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.35" metricValueMax="6.4" metricValueMin="6.3" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" unit="mm" value="6.35" valueMax="6.4" valueMin="6.3">6.3–6.4 mm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[422,557,858,883]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.35" metricValueMax="2.5" metricValueMin="2.2" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" unit="mm" value="2.35" valueMax="2.5" valueMin="2.2">2.2–2.5 mm</quantity>
wide across humeral angles. Color dull stramineous, with pair of small brown sublateral spots on pronotum near midlength (
<figureCitation box="[663,728,894,919]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1678,1700]" captionTargetBox="[158,1427,193,1655]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[158,1428,193,1657]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Dorsal and lateral habitus. A, B, Decliviassus bipunctatus sp. nov.; C, D, Decliviassus maculatus sp. nov.; E, F, Decliviassus nudus sp. nov.; G, H, Kanchanaburiassus maculatus sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/253712/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Fig. 
<number box="[714,728,895,919]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
A, B). 
<collectingCountry box="[803,859,894,919]" name="India" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Hind</collectingCountry>
tibia macrosetal rows PD, AD, and AV with 17, 12, and 
<number box="[202,230,931,955]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="13.0">13</number>
setae respectively; first hind tarsomere pecten with 
<number box="[842,856,930,955]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="5.0">5</number>
platellae. Pygofer appendage in lateral view with prominent posterior lobe and hooklike ventral projection (
<figureCitation box="[808,890,966,991]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1574,1596]" captionTargetBox="[190,1399,205,1542]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[177,1409,193,1552]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 10. The holotype of Decliviassus bipunctatus sp. nov. A. Genital capsule, lateral view; B. Aedeagus, lateral view; C. Style, lateral view; D. Subgenital plates, ventral view; E. Ventral process of pygofer side, caudolateral view; F. Apex of aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/253719/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Fig. 
<number box="[861,890,967,991]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
A). Subgenital plate with mesal margin trilobed, with few short, fine setae distally (
<figureCitation box="[544,626,1002,1027]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1574,1596]" captionTargetBox="[190,1399,205,1542]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[177,1409,193,1552]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 10. The holotype of Decliviassus bipunctatus sp. nov. A. Genital capsule, lateral view; B. Aedeagus, lateral view; C. Style, lateral view; D. Subgenital plates, ventral view; E. Ventral process of pygofer side, caudolateral view; F. Apex of aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/253719/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Fig. 
<number box="[598,626,1003,1027]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
A, D). Style apophysis in lateral view evenly tapered distally with apex bluntly rounded and short, obtusely angulate posteroventral projection preapically (
<figureCitation box="[1086,1168,1038,1063]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1574,1596]" captionTargetBox="[190,1399,205,1542]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[177,1409,193,1552]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 10. The holotype of Decliviassus bipunctatus sp. nov. A. Genital capsule, lateral view; B. Aedeagus, lateral view; C. Style, lateral view; D. Subgenital plates, ventral view; E. Ventral process of pygofer side, caudolateral view; F. Apex of aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/253719/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Fig. 
<number box="[1139,1168,1039,1063]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
C, 
<number box="[1200,1228,1039,1063]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="11.0">11</number>
B). Aedeagus with paired distal processes approximately as long as maximum width of shaft, extended ventrad along shaft and curved slightly laterad distally, shaft apex with short unpaired digitiform posterior projection; gonopore elongate, apical on posterior surface of shaft (
<figureCitation box="[445,530,1146,1171]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1574,1596]" captionTargetBox="[190,1399,205,1542]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[177,1409,193,1552]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 10. The holotype of Decliviassus bipunctatus sp. nov. A. Genital capsule, lateral view; B. Aedeagus, lateral view; C. Style, lateral view; D. Subgenital plates, ventral view; E. Ventral process of pygofer side, caudolateral view; F. Apex of aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/253719/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Figs 
<number box="[501,530,1147,1171]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
B, 
<number box="[562,590,1147,1171]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="11.0">11</number>
B).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
