<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,858,1602]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,273,1398,1423]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Notes.</emphasis>
The two male specimens listed above as ‘Other material’ are excluded from the 
<typeStatus box="[1219,1267,1399,1423]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">type</typeStatus>
series and are tentatively considered conspecific, but differ from the 
<typeStatus box="[771,869,1434,1459]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">holotype</typeStatus>
in lacking the digitiform posteroapical projection on the aedeagal shaft (
<figureCitation box="[417,501,1470,1495]" captionStart="FIGURE 11" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1843,1865]" captionTargetBox="[197,1392,419,1815]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[191,1396,411,1821]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 11. Decliviassus bipunctatus sp. nov. from Phetchabun. A. Aedeagus, style and connective, ventral view; B. Aedeagus, style and connective, lateral view; C. Ventral process of pygofer side, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/253720/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
Fig. 
<number box="[473,501,1471,1495]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="11.0">11</number>
</figureCitation>
B). The specimen from sample T 
<number box="[888,944,1470,1495]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" value="2415.0">2415</number>
also lacks the pair of brown spots on the pronotum present in the other two specimens and has the processes of the aedeagal shaft both extended to the right of the shaft. Such variation is here considered intraspecific. The species name refers to the two black spots on the pronotum.
</paragraph>
